===Etymology===
From {{der|en|enm|large}}, from {{der|en|fro|large}}, from {{der|en|la|larga}}, feminine of {{m|la|largus||abundant, plentiful, copious, large, much}}, of uncertain ultimate origin; see there for more. Mostly displaced {{cog|enm|stoor|stoor, stour|large, great}} (from {{cog|ang|stÅr}}) and {{m|enm|muchel||large, great}} (from {{cog|ang|myÄ‹el}}).
